Hokkaido Electric Power Co.'s Tomari nuclear power plant in Tomari Village, Hokkaido, Japan, on May 5. Japan had no nuclear-generated electricity for the first time in more than four decades after Tomari, its sole operating power reactor, was halted for scheduled maintenance. Visit  www.bloomberg.com/sustainability  for the latest from Bloomberg News about energy, natural resources and global b usiness.